headline: Steel Tariffs Not Hurting U.S. Manufacturing, Nucor Chief Says
summary: Higher tariffs have been effective at driving imported steel out of the U.S. without damaging steel-consuming industries, Nucor Chief Executive Leon Topalian said.  Imports accounted for around 14% of the U.S. steel market in November, down from about 25% a year earlier, according to government and industry data.  “We’ve seen import levels I’ve never seen in my 30 years at Nucor,” Topalian told analysts during a conference call.
